---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<Layout title="What Is EB-1A? | EB-1A Green Card Coach" description="Everything you need to know about the EB-1A visa — benefits, requirements, criteria, and how to apply.">

  <PageHero eyebrow="What is EB-1A?" heading="Known About" />

  <!-- ── Intro ── -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container eb1a-intro-grid">

      <div class="eb1a-intro-text">
        <p class="text-body">
          The United States offers a variety of visas for individuals seeking to live and work in the country,
          and the EB1A visa is one such option that is highly sought after by individuals in their field.
          Whether you're a scientist, artist, athlete, business professional, or educator, this comprehensive
          guide will take you through the ins and outs of the EB1A visa, covering everything you need to know
          to navigate the application process seamlessly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
          One key benefit of the EB1A visa is its flexibility — applicants can secure a green card without
          needing a job offer from a U.S. company. Moreover, opting for premium processing ensures a speedy
          review of your application within just 15 days.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
          In this comprehensive guide, we'll explore the ins and outs of the EB1A visa, covering everything
          you need to know to navigate the application process seamlessly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
          If you have any questions or need assistance with your EB1A visa, don't hesitate to reach out directly
          at <a href="mailto:contact@eb1agreencardcoach.com" class="inline-link">contact@eb1agreencardcoach.com</a>.
          Our team of experienced EB-1A Coaches is here to help you every step of the way.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-intro-image">
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-1.jpg" alt="EB-1A professional" class="content-img" width="520" height="380" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Sections 1 & 2 ── -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">1. What is the EB1A Visa?</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">
          The EB1A visa, also known as the Employment-Based First Preference Visa for Aliens of
          Extraordinary Ability, is a category of visa designed for individuals who demonstrate
          extraordinary ability in their field, whether it's arts, sciences, education, business,
          or athletics.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
          Unlike many other employment-based visas, the EB1A visa does not require a job offer from a
          U.S. employer. Instead, applicants can self-petition, meaning they can apply on their own
          behalf without sponsorship from an employer.
        </p>
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-2.jpg" alt="EB-1A Visa" class="content-img content-img--mt" width="520" height="300" />
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">2. What are the Benefits of an EB1A Visa?</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">The EB1A visa offers several benefits to individuals seeking to live and work in the United States:</p>
        <ul class="eb1a-benefit-list">
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            There is no necessity for a job offer from a U.S. employer
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Priority processing by USCIS
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Eligibility to apply for a green card (permanent residency) without the need for a labor certification
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Ability to include immediate family members (spouse and unmarried children under 21) as dependents
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            The ability to work for any employer within the United States in the same field of extraordinary ability
          </li>
        </ul>
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-3.jpg" alt="EB-1A Benefits" class="content-img content-img--mt" width="520" height="300" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 3 ── -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">3. What are the EB1A Visa Requirements? (How to Get an EB1A Visa)</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">To qualify for an EB1A visa, applicants must meet the following requirements:</p>
        <ul class="eb1a-benefit-list">
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Extraordinary ability in their field demonstrated by sustained national or international acclaim
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Documentation of their achievements and recognition in their field
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Intent to continue working in their field of extraordinary ability in the United States
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-body">
          Additionally, applicants must satisfy at least three out of the ten criteria outlined by USCIS,
          which include evidence of receipt of major awards, membership in associations that require
          outstanding achievements, published material about the applicant, participation as a judge of
          the work of others, original contributions of major significance, authorship of scholarly
          articles, displays of work at artistic exhibitions, performance in a leading or critical role
          for distinguished organizations, high salary, and commercial successes in the performing arts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-image-col">
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-4.jpg" alt="EB-1A Requirements" class="content-img" width="520" height="420" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 4 ── -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-image-col">
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-5.jpg" alt="EB-1A Criteria" class="content-img" width="520" height="420" />
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">4. Additional EB1A Criteria</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">Applicants must satisfy at least three out of the ten criteria outlined by USCIS:</p>
        <ol class="eb1a-numbered-list">
          <li>Receipt of significant awards or prizes in recognition of exemplary accomplishments</li>
          <li>Membership in prestigious associations that mandate exceptional achievements</li>
          <li>Coverage in professional or prominent trade publications</li>
          <li>Participation as a judge evaluating the work of peers</li>
          <li>Noteworthy contributions in original scientific, scholarly, artistic, athletic, or business realms</li>
          <li>Authorship of scholarly articles in professional or prominent trade publications</li>
          <li>Presentation of work at esteemed artistic exhibitions or showcases</li>
          <li>Engagement in pivotal roles for organizations of distinguished reputation</li>
          <li>Receiving a substantial salary significantly high relative to peers within the field</li>
          <li>Achieving commercial successes in the performing arts</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Sections 5 & 6 ── -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">5. How Does USCIS Decide Whether to Approve or Deny an EB1A Visa Petition?</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">
          USCIS evaluates EB1A visa petitions based on the evidence provided by the applicant to demonstrate
          their extraordinary ability in their field. The burden of proof lies with the applicant to establish
          their eligibility for the visa. USCIS assesses the credibility and relevance of the evidence provided
          and may issue a Request for Evidence (RFE) if additional documentation or clarification is needed.
          Ultimately, USCIS determines whether to approve or deny the petition based on the totality of the
          evidence presented.
        </p>
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-6.jpg" alt="USCIS decision" class="content-img content-img--mt" width="520" height="300" />
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">6. What Documents are Needed to Apply for an EB1A Visa?</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">Applicants must submit a comprehensive package of evidence:</p>
        <ul class="eb1a-benefit-list">
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Letters of recommendation from experts in the applicant's field
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Documentation of awards, honors, and other forms of recognition
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Published articles, books, or other scholarly works authored by the applicant
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Evidence of participation as a judge of the work of others
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Documentation of original contributions of major significance
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            Proof of commercial successes in the performing arts, if applicable
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-body">Additionally, applicants must complete Form I-140, Immigrant Petition for Alien Worker, and pay the required filing fee.</p>
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-7.jpg" alt="Documents needed" class="content-img content-img--mt" width="520" height="300" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 7 ── -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-image-col">
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-8.jpg" alt="How to apply" class="content-img" width="520" height="420" />
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">7. How to Apply for EB1A Visa</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <div class="apply-steps">
          <div class="apply-step">
            <p class="apply-step-title">Gather Evidence</p>
            <p class="text-body">Compile comprehensive documentation to support your petition, including letters of recommendation, awards, publications, and any other relevant materials.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apply-step">
            <p class="apply-step-title">Complete Form I-140</p>
            <p class="text-body">Fill out Form I-140, Immigrant Petition for Alien Worker, accurately and thoroughly. Include the required filing fee and supporting documents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apply-step">
            <p class="apply-step-title">Submit Petition</p>
            <p class="text-body">Send the completed Form I-140 and supporting documents to the appropriate USCIS service center.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apply-step">
            <p class="apply-step-title">Wait for USCIS Decision</p>
            <p class="text-body">USCIS will review your petition and determine whether to approve or deny it. They may issue a Request for Evidence (RFE) if additional information is needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apply-step">
            <p class="apply-step-title">Receive Visa</p>
            <p class="text-body">Upon approval, you will receive your EB1A visa, allowing you to live and work in the United States as a lawful permanent resident.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 8 — Conclusion ── -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container eb1a-two-col">

      <div class="eb1a-content-block">
        <h2 class="heading-2 eb1a-section-num">8. Conclusion</h2>
        <hr class="divider" />
        <p class="text-body">
          The EB1A visa offers a valuable opportunity for individuals with extraordinary abilities in their
          field to live and work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship. By meeting
          the stringent requirements and providing compelling evidence of their extraordinary ability,
          applicants can successfully obtain an EB1A visa and pursue their career goals in the United States.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body">
          However, navigating the application process can be complex, and seeking guidance from experienced
          immigration professionals is highly recommended to increase the likelihood of a successful outcome.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact-us" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: var(--sp-4); align-self: flex-start;">Request A Consultation</a>
      </div>

      <div class="eb1a-image-col">
        <img src="/images/EB-1A-What-Img-9.jpg" alt="Conclusion" class="content-img" width="520" height="380" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Shared two-col layout */
  .eb1a-intro-grid,
  .eb1a-two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-12);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .eb1a-intro-text { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-5); }

  .content-img { width: 100%; height: 340px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: var(--radius-md); display: block; }
  .content-img--mt { margin-top: var(--sp-6); }

  .eb1a-content-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-5); }
  .eb1a-image-col { display: flex; align-items: center; }

  .eb1a-section-num { font-size: clamp(20px, 2vw, 28px); color: var(--color-navy); }

  .inline-link { color: var(--color-primary); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

  /* Benefit list */
  .eb1a-benefit-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }

  .eb1a-benefit-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
  }

  .eb1a-benefit-list li svg { color: var(--color-primary); flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 4px; }

  /* Numbered list */
  .eb1a-numbered-list {
    list-style: decimal;
    padding-left: var(--sp-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }

  .eb1a-numbered-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    padding-left: var(--sp-2);
  }

  /* Apply steps */
  .apply-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-5); }

  .apply-step { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-2); }

  .apply-step-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    font-weight: var(--fw-bold);
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .eb1a-intro-grid,
    .eb1a-two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }

    .eb1a-image-col { order: -1; }
  }
</style>
